      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like your tomato plants might be suffering from a condition known as chlorosis, where the lower leaves are turning yellow due to a lack of essential nutrients, especially iron. This can often be a result of poor drainage or compacted soil, which hinders root growth and nutrient uptake. To help your plants, you might consider adding some compost to improve soil structure and fertility, or you could try a liquid iron supplement to address the nutrient deficiency. Keep an eye on the plants and see if the situation improves. If not, it might be time to consult a local gardening expert for more specific advice.",
